entries.title: Madonna wipes her Instagram in preparation for suspected tour announcement
entries.description: The Material Girl might be preparing to take on the material world -- on tour.

entries.title: Former Wagner commander flees to Norway and seeks asylum
Andrei Medvedev said he feared for his life after refusing to renew his service with the Russian mercenary group
entries.description: A former commander in Russia's Wagner private military company has fled to Norway and is seeking asylum after crossing that country's arctic border, according to Norwegian police and a Russian activist.

entries.title: 6 people, including a baby, were killed in a 'massacre' that is likely gang-related, California sheriff's office says
entries.description: At least six people, including a mother and her 6-month-old baby, are dead after an "early morning massacre" Monday in the town of Goshen, California, according to the Tulare County Sheriff's Office.

entries.title: UK government blocks Scotland's new gender recognition law
entries.description: The UK government has blocked a new law intended to allowed trans people in Scotland to change their legal gender without a medical diagnosis -- a controversial move that has added fuel to the already highly emotional debate over Scottish independence.

entries.title: Retired general on Dnipro attack: Another instance of Russia flat-out lying
entries.description: CNN military analyst Lt. Gen. Mark Hertling (Ret.) tells CNN's Kate Bolduan what type of missiles he believes Russia used in its attack on an apartment in Dnipro, Ukraine, and what Ukraine's next move should be.

entries.title: Mob boss walked out of hospital in custody after 30 years on the run
entries.description: Italy's most wanted man, mob boss Matteo Messina Denaro, was captured after 30 years on the run. Police took the 60-year-old into custody after a raid on a private hospital.

entries.title: Ukraine's ambassador to Australia condemns Russian flag display at the Australian Open
entries.description: Ukraine's ambassador to Australia has "strongly condemn[ed]" the Russian flag being displayed in the stands at the Australian Open.

entries.title: Armed men kidnap 50 women and girls foraging for food in Burkina Faso
entries.description: A group of women and girls foraging for wild fruits were abducted by armed men in separate incidents in Burkina Faso, the government said Monday.

entries.title: Worshipers killed as bomb detonates during DRC church service
entries.description: Worshipers at a church service in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) were killed Sunday when a bomb was detonated by a group with links to Islamic State, the government said.

entries.title: In parts of Ancient Greece, first-cousin marriage was not only allowed but encouraged, DNA shows
entries.description: If you wanted to hang on to your land in Bronze Age Greece, you could do worse than marry your cousin.

entries.title: A major oil exporter is hosting a UN climate summit. Opinions are divided
entries.description: This year's COP28 climate summit is mired in controversy, held in one of the world's biggest oil exporting nations -- the United Arab Emirates -- and headed by one of the most prominent faces in its oil industry.

entries.title: Black box recovered from Nepal plane crash wreckage
Dallas Zoo monkey enclosure fencing cut on same day as tampering that allowed leopard to escape, police say
entries.description: Fencing that was cut at the Dallas Zoo's clouded leopard habitat Friday -- resulting in the escape of one of the animals -- wasn't the only apparent tampering at the zoo that day, police said.

entries.title: Bitcoin rallies 25% as crypto markets rebound
entries.description: The bitcoin bulls are back.

entries.title: More than half of US states have cracked down on TikTok access from government devices
entries.description: More than half of all US states have partially or fully banned TikTok from government devices, according to a CNN analysis, reflecting a wave of recent clampdowns by governors and state agencies targeting the short-form video app.

entries.title: Selena Gomez responds to body shamers following Golden Globes appearance
entries.description: Selena Gomez brushed off online body shamers following her red carpet appearance at the Golden Globes on Tuesday.

entries.title: Stabbing of Asian student was motivated by race, suspect allegedly said. Now, another US community is pushing back on anti-AAPI hate
entries.description: The suspect in an unprovoked attack allegedly said she was motivated by race when she repeatedly stabbed the victim -- an Asian student at Indiana University -- last week on a city bus, according to court documents and a student group.

entries.title: MLK's son discusses controversial new monument honoring his mother and father
entries.description: Martin Luther King III joins CNN's Don Lemon to discuss "The Embrace," a new monument honoring his father and mother, Martin Luther King Jr. and Coretta Scott King.

entries.title: The steep plunge in used car prices -- what it means, and what's ahead
entries.description: Tracking used car prices is enough to give anyone whiplash.

entries.title: American detained in Iran begins hunger strike in appeal to Biden
entries.description: Siamak Namazi, an American wrongfully detained in Iran, is calling on President Joe Biden to take notice of US detainees there, launching a hunger strike to mark seven years since he was left behind in a prisoner swap that brought other Americans home. CNN's Kylie Atwood has the story.

entries.title: ER on the field: An inside look at how NFL medical teams prepare for a game day emergency
entries.description: When Buffalo Bills safety Damar Hamlin dropped to the ground from a cardiac arrest earlier this month, help was by his side in under 10 seconds to administer CPR.

entries.title: Gina Lollobrigida, legend of Italian cinema, dead at 95
entries.description: Italian screen legend Gina Lollobrigida has died at the age of 95, news agency ANSA reported, citing members of her family.

entries.title: Ukraine soccer club Shakhtar Donetsk launches $25m project for Mariupol soldiers after selling star player
entries.description: Ukrainian soccer club Shakhtar Donetsk has launched a $25M project for Mariupol soldiers and their families, the club announced Monday.

entries.title: Spending the night in an igloo, in the Alps. Sounds cool, but is it?
entries.description: Spending the night in an igloo sounds cool. And it is, though mainly literally.

entries.title: Al Brown, best known as Stan Valchek in 'The Wire,' dead at 83
entries.description: Veteran actor Al Brown, who became famous for his role in the hit TV show "The Wire," has died at age 83.

entries.title: 23 years ago, another 6-year-old boy fired a gun in school. The victim was his classmate
entries.description: When authorities in Newport News, Virginia, announced on January 6 that a 6-year-old boy brought a gun to school and shot his teacher, sending her to the hospital, the country was stunned. The city's mayor said it was nearly impossible to grapple with what happened. The police chief called the case "unprecedented."

entries.title: UK Metropolitan Police officer admits to dozens of sexual offenses including rape
entries.description: An officer with London's Metropolitan Police, David Carrick, has admitted to 49 offenses including 24 counts of rape over an 18-year period, the UK's PA Media news agency reported on Monday.

entries.title: LeBron James becomes second player in NBA history to reach 38,000 career points
entries.description: LeBron James has become the second NBA player in history to pass 38,000 career points, moving closer to Kareem Abdul-Jabbar's all-time record.

entries.title: Best red carpet fashion at the 2023 Critics' Choice Awards
'Literally theft': French baker bemoans soaring energy bills
entries.description: In December 2022, the baguette -- France's national dish -- was added to UNESCO's list of "intangible cultural heritage of humanity." But high inflation has hiked energy prices and bakeries are struggling to pay their energy bills so they can keep baking the symbolic French bread. CNN's Melissa Bell reports.

entries.title: Barcelona wins Spanish Super Cup after beating Real Madrid 3-1 in final hosted by Saudi Arabia
entries.description: Barcelona produced an impressive performance to beat Real Madrid 3-1 and lift the Spanish Super Cup on Sunday.

entries.title: Kostyuk won't shake hands with Russian, Belarusian tennis players
entries.description: As Russian missiles continue to pound her country, Ukraine's number two tennis player Marta Kostyuk says she will not shake hands with tour rivals from Russia and Belarus who she feels have not done enough to speak out against the invasion.

entries.title: Fed up with facial recognition cameras monitoring your every move? Italian fashion may have the answer
entries.description: The red-headed man wearing what looks like the ultimate Christmas sweater walks up to the camera. A yellow quadrant surrounds him. Facial recognition software immediately identifies the man as ... a giraffe?

entries.title: Davos draws record crowds, but its relevance is fading
entries.description: Every year, business leaders, billionaires and politicians gather in Davos, Switzerland under the banner of forging ties that can help solve global problems.

entries.title: 'The ball boy took my racket': Nadal suffers dampener snafu at Australian Open
entries.description: It wasn't all plain sailing for Rafael Nadal in his first-round victory at the Australian Open on Monday.

entries.title: New York man who broke into a school to shelter more than 20 people from deadly blizzard is awarded Super Bowl tickets by the Buffalo Bills
entries.description: A man who saved more than 20 people during the deadly snowstorm that shrouded Erie County, New York, in December has been thanked for his actions with tickets to the Super Bowl gifted to him in part by the NFL's Buffalo Bills.

entries.title: Bullying at school: What parents can do to help victims and stop bullies
entries.description: There's a crisis of bullying in US schools, and the solution is learning what to do before it happens.

entries.title: Americans see Martin Luther King Jr. as a hero now, but that wasn't the case during his lifetime
entries.description: Martin Luther King Jr. was a civil rights leader and an American hero. Almost every American adult (95% in CBS News polling) believes he was an important figure in US history.

entries.title: Arsenal goalkeeper Aaron Ramsdale kicked by fan following North London derby
entries.description: Arsenal goalkeeper Aaron Ramsdale appeared to be kicked in the back by a spectator following Arsenal's 2-0 victory against Tottenham on Sunday at the Tottenham Hotspur Stadium in London.

entries.title: Tiny, foot-long dwarf boa identified in Ecuador is new to science
entries.description: Scientists have identified a tiny new species of dwarf boa living in the Ecuadorian Amazon that even a snake hater could love: These small reptiles are just a foot long.

entries.title: Is this the end of an era for Liverpool?
entries.description: The World Cup was a welcome pause for Liverpool Football Club. A moment to reset and reassess after a torrid start to the season. Defeats and lackluster performances had made it an unpalatable autumn. Surely, the reasoning went, things could not get worse.

entries.title: The 'Blue Monday' depression peak isn't real, but seasonal blues are. Here's what to do
entries.description: As if we needed any more reason to ruminate over pandemic life's daily plights, today (January 16) is Blue Monday — the third Monday of January, which is rumored to be the most depressing day of the year.

entries.title: Mafia boss Matteo Messina Denaro arrested in Sicily
entries.description: Matteo Messina Denaro, one of the bosses of the Cosa Nostra Mafia in Sicily and Italy's most wanted man, has been arrested by police while being treated in a private health clinic in Palermo, prosecutor Maurizio de Lucia said Monday.

entries.title: China says 60,000 people have died of Covid since early December
Why this green burial startup wants to turn people into trees
entries.description: The human body can be measured by many metrics. One is roughly one cubic yard (0.8 cubic meters) -- that's how much compost a corpse produces when combined with plant material and allowed to rot down for six to 10 weeks.

entries.title: Former Afghan lawmaker Mursal Nabizada shot dead at her home in Kabul
entries.description: Former Afghan lawmaker Mursal Nabizada and her security guard were shot dead her home in Kabul early Sunday morning, according to Kabul police.

entries.title: Gucci hits runway as fashion world awaits new designer

entries.title: Another atmospheric river lashes California, renewing flooding concerns in state where storms have left at least 19 dead
entries.description: Another atmospheric river has arrived in storm-battered California, bringing renewed flooding fears, possible landslides and treacherous travel to the state Monday where a relentless string of storms has already delivered widespread damage and left at least 19 dead in recent weeks.

entries.title: Coco Gauff and Emma Raducanu set up tantalizing second round Australian Open clash with opening wins
entries.description: Two of tennis' most exciting young players, Coco Gauff and Emma Raducanu, will face off in the Australian Open second round after they both won their opening matches on Monday.

entries.title: It's now minus 50 in the world's coldest city
entries.description: Thought your winter was cold? Temperatures in the world's coldest city have plunged to minus 50 degrees Celsius (-58 Fahrenheit).

entries.title: One Chinese province spent $22 billion on eliminating Covid before policy U-turn
entries.description: A number of regional governments in China have revealed the enormous sums they've spent on fighting the pandemic, reinforcing a previous state media report suggesting that mounting costs were a key reason why the country abruptly abandoned its zero-Covid policy.

entries.description: • Video appears to show plane's final moments before crash

entries.description: University of Alabama basketball player Darius Miles has been arrested and charged with murder in connection with a shooting near the campus Sunday which left a 23-year-old woman dead, Tuscaloosa law enforcement announced.

entries.title: Indonesia sends warship to monitor Chinese coast guard vessel
